---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Code of Conduct — DevCongress" description="DevCongress community code of conduct.">
  <header class="coc-nav">
    <div class="container coc-nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="coc-logo">
        <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="DevCongress" height="36" />
      </a>
      <a href="/" class="coc-back">← Back</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container coc-body">
    <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
    <h1 class="heading-serif coc-heading">Code of Conduct</h1>

    <div class="coc-content">
      <h2>Our Pledge</h2>
      <p>DevCongress is a community built on respect, collaboration, and the shared belief that builders across Africa deserve a space to grow together. We pledge to make participation in our community a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body size, disability, ethnicity, gender identity and expression, level of experience, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity and orientation.</p>

      <h2>Our Standards</h2>
      <p><strong>We expect community members to:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use welcoming and inclusive language</li>
        <li>Respect differing viewpoints and experiences</li>
        <li>Accept constructive criticism gracefully</li>
        <li>Focus on what is best for the community</li>
        <li>Show empathy and kindness to fellow members</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>We do not tolerate:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Harassment, intimidation, or discrimination in any form</li>
        <li>Sexualised language, imagery, or unwelcome advances</li>
        <li>Trolling, insulting or derogatory comments, and personal attacks</li>
        <li>Publishing others' private information without explicit permission</li>
        <li>Sustained disruption of community discussions or events</li>
        <li>Any conduct that would be considered inappropriate in a professional setting</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Scope</h2>
      <p>This Code of Conduct applies in all DevCongress spaces — including our Slack community, events, meetups, online forums, and any other space where you represent DevCongress or its community.</p>

      <h2>Enforcement</h2>
      <p>Community leaders are responsible for clarifying and enforcing these standards. Instances of unacceptable behaviour may be reported to the DevCongress team at <a href="mailto:hello@devcongress.org">hello@devcongress.org</a>. All complaints will be reviewed promptly and handled with discretion.</p>
      <p>Community leaders may take any action they deem appropriate, including a warning, temporary suspension, or permanent removal from the community.</p>

      <h2>Attribution</h2>
      <p>This Code of Conduct is adapted from the <a href="https://www.contributor-covenant.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Contributor Covenant</a>, version 2.1.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .coc-nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    background: var(--bg);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--black);
    padding-block: var(--s4);
  }
  .coc-nav-inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
  .coc-back {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-mid);
    transition: color 150ms ease;
  }
  .coc-back:hover { color: var(--pink); }

  .coc-body {
    max-width: 760px;
    padding-block: var(--s9);
  }

  .coc-heading {
    font-size: clamp(var(--text-3xl), 6vw, var(--text-4xl));
    margin-bottom: var(--s8);
  }

  .coc-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    color: var(--text);
    margin-top: var(--s8);
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
    padding-bottom: var(--s3);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--black);
  }

  .coc-content p {
    color: var(--text-mid);
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
    line-height: var(--leading-body);
  }

  .coc-content ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin-bottom: var(--s5);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--s2);
  }

  .coc-content li {
    color: var(--text-mid);
    padding-left: var(--s5);
    position: relative;
    line-height: var(--leading-body);
  }
  .coc-content li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--pink);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .coc-content a {
    color: var(--pink);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  .coc-content strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
